      <div class="ds-field">
        <div class="ds-sub-label">Ask my system — special input</div>
        <div class="ds-ask-bar">
          <input class="ds-ask-input" type="text" placeholder="Ask my system anything…" />
          <button class="ds-ask-btn">Ask →</button>
        </div>
        <span class="ds-helper">Full-pill bar with yellow CTA button inside</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ────────────────────────────────────────
       13 · ICONOGRAPHY
  ──────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="ds-section" id="icons">
    <div class="ds-section-header">
      <span class="ds-section-num">13</span>
      <h2 class="ds-section-title">Iconography</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="ds-card">
      <table class="ds-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Rule</th><th>Guidance</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Primary system</td><td>Lucide Icons (CDN) — 2px stroke, 24px grid, SVG only</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Style</td><td>Outline/stroke icons — matches the doodle line-art aesthetic</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Sizes</td><td>16px (dense UI) · 20px (default) · 24px (prominent)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Color</td><td>Inherits from text color; yellow used for accent icons</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Custom doodle icons</td><td>Hand-drawn SVGs for signature brand moments (Ask, dashboard)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Prohibited</td><td>No emoji as UI icons · No PNG · No filled icons</td></tr>
          <tr><td>SVG in code</td><td>Use inline SVG for <code class="ds-code">currentColor</code> inheritance. Import with <code class="ds-code">?url</code> only for decorative images.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ────────────────────────────────────────
       14 · DISCREPANCIES & DECISIONS
  ──────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="ds-section" id="discrepancies">
    <div class="ds-section-header">
      <span class="ds-section-num">14</span>
      <h2 class="ds-section-title">Discrepancies & decisions</h2>
    </div>
    <p style="font-size:var(--text-sm);color:var(--fg-secondary);margin-bottom:var(--space-6);">
      Differences found between the live project and the Jeen Design System spec.
    </p>

    <div class="disc-card">
      <div class="disc-card-header">
        <span class="ds-badge ds-badge-success">Resolved</span>
        <h3 class="disc-card-title">--fg-tertiary: gray-500 → gray-400 (WCAG fix)</h3>
      </div>
      <p class="disc-card-body">Project had <code class="ds-code">--fg-tertiary: gray-500 (#6A6A60)</code> which fails WCAG AA on dark (#0A0A0A) backgrounds. DS spec uses gray-400 (#9A9A90, ~5:1). <strong>Decision: applied DS value to main.</strong></p>
    </div>

    <div class="disc-card">
      <div class="disc-card-header">
        <span class="ds-badge ds-badge-success">Resolved</span>
        <h3 class="disc-card-title">Nav CTA shadow: shadow-lg → shadow-sm</h3>
      </div>
      <p class="disc-card-body">DS preview showed smaller 2px 2px shadow on nav CTA vs the larger 5px used in project. <strong>Decision: use DS-preview (2px default, 3px hover) — feels more proportionate for a small nav element.</strong></p>
    </div>

    <div class="disc-card">
      <div class="disc-card-header">
        <span class="ds-badge ds-badge-success">Resolved</span>
        <h3 class="disc-card-title">Card hover lift: translateY(-3px) → -2px</h3>
      </div>
      <p class="disc-card-body">DS spec defines 2px lift on card hover. Project had 3px. <strong>Decision: reduced to -2px to match DS spec.</strong></p>
    </div>

    <div class="disc-card">
      <div class="disc-card-header">
        <span class="ds-badge ds-badge-success">Resolved</span>
        <h3 class="disc-card-title">Hero badge style: ghost (current) vs solid yellow (DS)</h3>
      </div>
      <p class="disc-card-body">DS spec shows hero role badge as solid yellow pill. Live project uses ghost style (transparent bg, gray border). <strong>Decision: keep current ghost style — it feels less heavy in the hero.</strong></p>
    </div>

    <div class="disc-card">
      <div class="disc-card-header">
        <span class="ds-badge ds-badge-yellow">Open</span>
        <h3 class="disc-card-title">Project-only tokens: code block, HR</h3>
      </div>
      <p class="disc-card-body">The diary page introduces tokens not in the original DS: inverted code blocks (black bg, white text), styled HRs (gray-300 border). These are project additions — consider adding them to the DS token set formally.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="disc-card">
      <div class="disc-card-header">
        <span class="ds-badge ds-badge-yellow">Open</span>
        <h3 class="disc-card-title">Ghost badges not in DS spec</h3>
      </div>
      <p class="disc-card-body">The Playground section uses ghost-style category labels (transparent bg, gray-300 border) not defined in the DS badge set. The DS only specifies solid variants (yellow, dark, outline, gray, success, error). Consider adding Ghost and Coming-soon as official variants.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="disc-card">
      <div class="disc-card-header">
        <span class="ds-badge ds-badge-yellow">Open</span>
        <h3 class="disc-card-title">Doodle illustrations: placeholders only</h3>
      </div>
      <p class="disc-card-body">DS spec calls for hand-drawn SVG doodles as decorative layer (1–3 per section, black line art). Currently only <code class="ds-code">feather_copy.svg</code> and <code class="ds-code">feather_check.svg</code> are in use. Full doodle illustration set to be provided by Jeen.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

</div><!-- end .ds-page -->

<!-- Footer -->
<div class="ds-footer">
  <div class="ds-footer-inner" style="justify-content: center;">
    <a href="#" onclick="window.scrollTo({ top: 0, behavior: 'smooth' }); return false;" class="ds-footer-link">↑ Top</a>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Floating TOC -->
<nav class="toc" aria-label="Page sections">
  {['context','principles','colors','typography','spacing','shadows','backgrounds','buttons','badges','cards','inputs','icons','discrepancies'].map((id) => (
    <button class="toc-dot" onclick={`document.getElementById('${id}').scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth'})`} title={id}>{id}</button>
  ))}
</nav>

<script>
  // Highlight active TOC dot on scroll
  const sections = document.querySelectorAll('.ds-section');
  const dots = document.querySelectorAll('.toc-dot');
  const obs = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
    entries.forEach(e => {
      if (e.isIntersecting) {
        const idx = [...sections].indexOf(e.target);
        dots.forEach((d, i) => d.classList.toggle('active', i === idx));
      }
    });
  }, { rootMargin: '-30% 0px -60% 0px' });
  sections.forEach(s => obs.observe(s));
</script>

</Layout>
